FT-IR spectra of free H2L and 1 were also studied (Fig. S3). FT-IR band located 3421 cm−1 indicates the existence of coordination and lattice water molecules. The band centered at 1710 cm−1 is the absorption of the C-O bond, proving the existence of uncoordinated carboxyl groups [37,38]. The band centered at 3122 cm−1 and at 1590 cm−1 can be ascribed to C-H stretching vibration and skeleton vibration of benzene ring, respectively. The band centered at 835 cm−1 is the characteristic absorption of benzene. The bands centered at 630 cm−1 prove the existence of triazole rings [39–44]. In order to better explain the structure, composition, and performance of 1, we also describe its various forms of 1. The size and morphology of 1 were determined by scanning electron microscope (SEM) and Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) (Fig. 5
                         and Fig. 6
                        ). High-magnification SEM image and TEM images show the main block structure and rod structure exist in complex 1 [45–50]. Through the help of image processing software Image J, the block structure can be analyzed that the 1 has the block structure length of 1.33–2.15 μm and the rod-like structure with a length of 1.94–8.71 μm. Particle size distribution table is also listed in Table S3.

In addition, according to Stern-Volmer equation, the relationship between fluorescence intensity and antibiotics NZF was drawn. The SV curve of NZF is approximately linear in the concentration range of 0–1.5 mM. According to the experimental data shown in Fig. 9
                        , In order to quantitatively demonstrate the sensitivity, the quenching efficiency can be estimated utilizing the Stern-Volmer (SV) formula, I0/I = Ksv[A] + 1, where I and I0 are considered as the emission intensities of 1 in the suspended aqueous solutions with and without NZF [60]. [A] is considered as NZF molar concentration, and Ksv is considered as the quenching coefficient. The Stern-Volmer plot for NZF is typically linear at the low concentrations with high Ksv value 5.0 × 106 M−1 (R2 = 0.996). The discriminative sensing of Nitrofurazone is not obviously affected by the addition of the other different analytes. The PXRD pattern of 1 was determined during the detection process that is in well consistent with the theoretical spectrum, which also shows that the structure of 1 is not changed (Fig. 10
                        ).
